## Priority: Critical

Conditional rendering is incomplete without `v-else` and `v-else-if`. Currently only `v-if` is supported; the others are explicitly rejected in `builder_validate.mbt`.

## Scope

- Parse `v-else` and `v-else-if` directives in template builder
- Track sibling elements to validate correct ordering (must follow `v-if` or `v-else-if`)
- Generate conditional branching in both client (`@vm_dom`) and server (`@luna_core`) codegen

## Example

```html
<template>
  <div v-if='count > 0'>positive</div>
  <div v-else-if='count == 0'>zero</div>
  <div v-else>negative</div>
</template>
```

## Files to modify

- `src/compiler/template/builder_validate.mbt` — remove rejection, add validation
- `src/compiler/template/builder.mbt` — sibling tracking
- `src/compiler/codegen/nodes.mbt` — conditional codegen
- `src/compiler/common/types.mbt` — extend `TemplateElement` if needed